// A bare untyped list literal is not assignable to []byte; only the
// []byte{...} spelling is (fix round: this used to typecheck by smuggling
// a boxed Value::List past the checker via the byte int-literal implicit,
// see tests/golden/eval/bytes-str-smuggled-list-fault.nv's history and
// docs/specs/2026-07-13-bytes-design.md's literal-rule section). []int
// never implicitly becomes []byte, same as int never implicitly becomes
// byte (spec 5.10).
fn takesBytes(b []byte) bool {
    return b.contains(byte(1))
}

fn main() {
    print(takesBytes([1, 2]))
}
